@startuml object_safety_to_ldr_health_range_bucket_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Object Safety To LDR Health Range Bucket Signal Flow\n(object-safety input + ADAS domain state -> LDR health and range-bucket publication)

participant "Lidar input bus" as LidarIn #F4F7FB
participant "ADAS domain state" as AdasDom #E8F0FE
participant "LDR\nlidar-state owner" as LDR #E8F7E8
participant "Lidar state bus" as LdrBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers /\nperception readers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== LDR Inputs ==

LidarIn -> LDR : frmLidarInputMsg\nTargetDetected / Confidence / EventCode
AdasDom -> LDR : frmAdasDomainStateMsg\nWarningPathStatus / E2eHealthState / FailSafeMode
activate LDR
LDR -> LDR : objectSafetyInputStale =\nethIsRecentTick(gObjectSafetyRxTsMs, 300)
LDR -> LDR : pathReady = lidarPathReady()\nfrom warning path / E2E / fail-safe
LDR -> LDR : if stale or path blocked then\nconfidence/event/track = 0
LDR -> LDR : derive health from\npathReady, fail-safe, track-valid, confidence
LDR -> LDR : derive freeSpaceClass and rangeBucket
note right of LDR
Representative gating inputs
- TargetDetected
- Confidence
- EventCode
- WarningPathStatus
- E2eHealthState
- FailSafeMode
end note

== LDR Publish ==

LDR -> LdrBus : frmLidarStateMsg\nLidarHealth / TargetDetected /\nFreeSpaceClass / Confidence / RangeBucket
note right of LDR
Representative outputs
- LidarHealth
- TargetDetected
- Confidence
- RangeBucket
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

LdrBus -> Obs : perception visibility /\nADAS and observer consumption
deactivate LDR

note over LidarIn, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Object-safety input and ADAS domain state reach LDR
2. LDR checks path readiness and fail-safe posture
3. LDR derives health, confidence class, and range bucket
4. LDR publishes frmLidarStateMsg for downstream readers
end note

@enduml
